# alias: test
# button-text: Test 4NT
# gib-works: true
# bba-works: true
# auction-filter: Auction.....\n1D +Pass +1H +2S +Pass +4S +4N
# convention-card-ns: 21GF-GIB
# convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB

/*@chat
--- Test: Can GIB bid 4NT (Unusual NT) after 1D-P-1H-2S-P-4S?
GIB says 4NT = Unusual NT: 5+ C, 5+ D, 4+ H, 18+ TP
But 5+5+4 = 14 > 13 cards, so the shape is impossible.
Testing with 4H + 5D + 4C (0-4-5-4) and 18+ TP.
@chat*/

dealer south

#include "script/TP"

# South opens 1D: 12-14 TP, 3+ diamonds, passes over 2S
sD = diamonds(south)>3 and diamonds(south)>=clubs(south)
sNoMajor = spades(south)<5 and hearts(south)<5
sNT = hcp(south)>14 and hcp(south)<17 and shape(south,any 5332 +any 4432 +any 4333 -5xxx -x5xx)
sOpens1D = sD and sNoMajor and not sNT and hcp(south)>11 and hcp(south)<15

# North responds 1H, then wants to bid 4NT
# GIB says: 5+ C, 5+ D, 4+ H, 18+ TP -- but 5+5+4=14 is impossible
# Try the closest shape: 0-4-5-4 with big points
nShape = spades(north)==0 and hearts(north)==4 and diamonds(north)>4 and clubs(north)>3
nStrong = hcp(north)>15 and tpNorth>17

# East overcalls 2S: 5+ spades, 10+ TP
eOvercall = spades(east)>4 and hcp(east)>7 and tpEast>9 and tpEast<17

# West raises to 4S: 3+ spades, Law of Total Tricks
wRaise = spades(west)>2 and tpWest<17

sOpens1D and nShape and nStrong and eOvercall and wRaise

produce 40
action
printoneline,
